v:4 c:$ m:T03-velocity-control role:dev x:vue3/typescript
gate: LOCKED

task: Turn the disabled Velocity toolbar button into a working velocity control

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
out:
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/components/PianoRollView.vue

depends: [T01-pianoroll-tool-api]

context: |
  PianoRollView.vue L100-114: a Velocity <button> that is hardcoded `disabled`
  with no handler. piano-roll.ts mousedown plays at hardcoded velocity 100.
  T01 added setClickVelocity(v). This task surfaces a control that drives it.

  Decision: a 3-step velocity toggle (soft / med / loud → 60 / 100 / 120) keeps
  the toolbar compact and matches the icon (the up/down arrows already drawn).
  No new slider component needed; reuse the existing button as a cycle control.

steps:
  1. Add ref:  const clickVelocity = ref(100)
  2. Add method velocityCycle() that rotates 60 → 100 → 120 → 60 and calls
     pianoRoll?.setClickVelocity(clickVelocity.value).
  3. Remove `disabled` from the Velocity button; add @click="velocityCycle".
  4. Show the current level: add a small label inside the button (e.g. the
     numeric value, or a 1/2/3 dot) OR a :title that states current velocity.
     Keep it visually consistent with the other two tool buttons.
  5. On mount, call pianoRoll.setClickVelocity(clickVelocity.value) after
     pianoRoll is constructed so engine + UI start in sync at 100.

done:
  - Velocity button is enabled and cycles 60/100/120 on click
  - Notes played via canvas use the selected velocity (audible loudness changes)
  - Current level is visible (label or title)
  - tsc --noEmit passes
